              The first sale never fell through, that is a pure lie. He received the money and never got back to me (since there was no auction I had no proof of a deal and as I live overseas he realised he could just ignore me and keep the money). Until I won this bid for the computer. If this hadn't happened he would have never contacted me again, nor would have offered a refund of course. AFter the conclusion of the computer sale, he even threatened if I didn't provide a shipping address in the next few days, the auction would fall through and he would not refund the money nor ship the computer. Luckily he got my address in the next few hours and told me PC would be shipped on the next Monday.<br><br>The money has now been sent for over TWO months and PC still not received. During these two months I received one email to confirm the computer had been shipped, then waited 6 weeks without any answer from him. After another of my mails I got an answer telling me he was talking with the customs and I still didn't get any answer. The auction was for a $400 computer, and I sent $600, which means I sent $200 for shipping and handling and prompt service. Still two months later nothing was received with very few information about the going of the deal. <br><br>Finally as it seems EQSTOCK doesn't seem very motivated to ship this PC and take care of this case promptly, I offered twice to get a refund of only $550 with Western Union, where the other $50 would be for the WU fees.<br><br>I have purchased many items over playerauctions, where my feedback is currently of 8. I never had any problems until I gave my trust to EQSTOCK, which really doesnt seem to care at all about this situation. Who knows maybe using this board will have more impact than my emails to him.<br><br>
