              I would like to explain situation here as people are thinking that I tried to scam him on a computer.  Original sale was for a EQ account I was selling for somebody that tried to put a scam on me.  I sold account and turned over funds to the person he gave me account info.  When I checked account items were not all their.  At the time vallon sent payment and I allready accepted it to turn over to the original seller.  Original seller had gotten funds allready through western union.  Now I got no replys from other seller so vallon got no replys from me.  Vallon then bidded on another auction of mine to get more attention from me.  Now after trying to resolve issuse I said his funds will go to the PC he bidded on.  Now when I said you will be getting the PC instead of the eq account he agreed to that.  I told him I was checking with shipping and customs. <br> Now sending a pc overseas takes awhile like 3 weeks.  After explaining this to him and responding to him what was transpiring he still insisted of me scamming him.  I Sent 3 emails telling him I was checking with customs of how to get the PC out of US with out any laws being broken.  Customs are the type of people that dont get right back to you.  Now he went and bidded on another PC to to get more attention.  Now to me he never intened on buying PC's just wanted more attention from me.  <br><br>Listing each PC's cost more more than $35 so I offerd a solution which you can see he refused.  He insisted I was going to scam him again.  Now i sold close to 20 computers here with no complaints except him.  After telling him shipping was $308 and would take 3 weeks to get to him he asked for refund.  After considerations and seeing he would not fret and give in to paying that much I offerd refund of the EQ account sale.  As stated in my auctions are people who bought these machines from me and I have not scammed.  Vallon threw empty threats of filling more IFCC reports if I didnt honor the PC sale enven though he knew he wasnt going to buy the PC's. <br><br>As for asking for address so many times is I get close to 300 emails a day about sales.  It's real hard to manage all the address's that come in.  Second my job takes me out of town atleast twice a month away from a internet connection, so responses are ruff at times.  <br><br>So people who check this now know the whole story about this .  Would most scammers come to a board to explain? NO! None of them do.   I am no scammer and not going to start.  I just move overstocked  inventory for mine and my brothers business even at a loss sometimes.  Any questions email me for my sales and would gladly answer any questions.  To ensure my sales any them can and will be shipped COD to ensure your safety of the sale.<br><br><br>This issue has been resolved with a refund of the EQ account.  Vallon agreed to pay the posting charges on the 2 PC aucitons. Refund wasnt offered earlier as he bidded and asked for the PC's.   Both of us agreed upon that and this matter has been resolved in a civil manner now.  Nobody here intened to scam anybody and we both are on a common ground now.<br><br>EQSTOCK<br><br><P ID="edit"><FONT SIZE=-1><EM>Edited by eqstock on 06/25/01 08:57 PM (server time).</EM></FONT></P>
